<% help_title "Help on #{ PcpCategory.model_name.human }" %>
  <div class="container">
    <%= helpcrumbs %>
    <%= help_header %>
    <p class="lead">Create and Maintain Present-Comment Process (PCP) Categories</p>
    <p>For general information on the PCP, see <%= link_to_help :pcp_general, 'PCP - The Present-Comment Process' -%>.</p>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>An PCP Category represents the (implicit or explicit) agreement between two project groups
      to participate in a process where a PCP Subject (e.g. a document or a site) is presented by the
      <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id )-%> to the 
      <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_group_id )-%> for review, comments and
      possibly final approval.</p>
    <p>PCP Categories are used to group PCP Subjects, for example, by the same originating and
      receiving project groups: All reviews of project documents by the client's organisation
      could be one PCP Category; another PCP Category would be all reviews of civil works
      documents by the systems groups; again another PCP Category would be all
      internal reviews within a specific project group.</p>
    <p>Another, important purpose for PCP Categories is the reporting aspect: Statistics are
      generated by PCP Category, and within each PCP Category, by the two participating
      project groups.</p>
    <p>The assignment of a specific PCP Category to a PCP Subject can be changed later by the
      owner of that PCP Subject - provided she has also access to the
      <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id )-%> of the new PCP Category.</p>
    <p>The following attributes are administered per PCP Category:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :id ) -%> is the unique identifier of each 
        individual PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :label ) -%> is the name of the PCP Category.
        The link here will lead to all PCP Subjects within this PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_group_id ) -%> is the project group
        providing comments and observations on the PCP Subjects in this PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id ) -%> is the project group
        presenting the PCP Subjects to be reviewed and commented on. This is group also provides the
        responses to any observations and comments.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_owner_id )-%> is the default owner for
        the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_group_id )-%> for any new PCP Subjects
        in this PCP Category. This parameter is required to ensure that there is always an owner defined
        for any PCP Subject.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_owner_id )-%> is the principal contact
        of the PCP for the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id )-%>. This
        user (account) has the permission to add PCP Subjects to this PCP Category.</li>
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_deputy_id )-%> can be used to define a
        default deputy for the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :c_owner_id )-%>.
      <li><%= help_param PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_deputy_id )-%> can be used to define a
        default deputy for the <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_owner_id )-%>.
    </ul>
    <h3>Permissions and Access</h3>
    <p>All users may view the information on each PCP Category. Only users with the specific
      permission to add and edit PCP Category items may create and modify PCP Category attributes.</p>
    <p>Users who want to create PCP Subjects for a specific PCP Category, need explicit update
      permission for this PCP Category's <%= help_term PcpCategory.human_attribute_name( :p_group_id )-%>
      in order to do so.</p>
    <%= help_footer FEATURE_ID_PCP_CATEGORIES %>
  </div> <!-- /container -->

